WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.160 align:middle line:90%


00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:18.850 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations,"

00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:21.570 align:middle line:10%
coming to you live from Boulder,
Colorado at the Gaiam Studios

00:00:21.570 --> 00:00:22.370 align:middle line:10%
here.

00:00:22.370 --> 00:00:24.230 align:middle line:10%
And since this is a
live, interactive show,

00:00:24.230 --> 00:00:25.960 align:middle line:10%
I encourage you
to connect with us

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:28.390 align:middle line:10%
and communicate with us
through Facebook and Twitter.

00:00:28.390 --> 00:00:30.790 align:middle line:10%
Many of you have already done
that, so thank you so much.

00:00:30.790 --> 00:00:32.248 align:middle line:10%
And keep the comments
and questions

00:00:32.248 --> 00:00:33.700 align:middle line:10%
coming throughout the show.

00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:35.090 align:middle line:90%
So let me ask you a question.

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:38.380 align:middle line:84%
Do you find it hard
to make changes?

00:00:38.380 --> 00:00:41.500 align:middle line:84%
Do you keep doing the same
things over and over again

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:45.100 align:middle line:84%
that bother you, but
then you know better,

00:00:45.100 --> 00:00:46.697 align:middle line:90%
and you keep doing it anyway?

00:00:46.697 --> 00:00:48.280 align:middle line:84%
Do you find yourself
in that position?

00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:51.130 align:middle line:84%
Well, today we're going to talk
about how the brain evolves

00:00:51.130 --> 00:00:53.800 align:middle line:84%
and how to actually make
changes in the brain,

00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:55.660 align:middle line:84%
so we can break some
of these old patterns,

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:57.730 align:middle line:90%
and better yet, create new ones.

00:00:57.730 --> 00:00:59.920 align:middle line:84%
And joining me is
Dr. Joe Dispenza.

00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:01.090 align:middle line:90%
He's a neuroscientist.

00:01:01.090 --> 00:01:03.260 align:middle line:84%
He's an expert on brain
functionality and brain

00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:04.060 align:middle line:90%
chemistry.

00:01:04.060 --> 00:01:06.160 align:middle line:84%
He's the author of
the book, "Breaking

00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:08.380 align:middle line:84%
the Habit of Being
Yourself," and get this,

00:01:08.380 --> 00:01:09.820 align:middle line:90%
I love this subtitle--

00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:12.650 align:middle line:84%
"How to Lose Your Mind
and Create a New One."

00:01:12.650 --> 00:01:13.723 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:01:13.723 --> 00:01:14.640 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for joining me.

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:15.370 align:middle line:90%
>>JOE DISPENZA: Thank you, Lisa.

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:16.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely great book.

00:01:16.620 --> 00:01:18.700 align:middle line:90%
And this is your latest release.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:20.560 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a little
bit about the book?

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:22.852 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well the second
book, "Breaking the Habit,"

00:01:22.852 --> 00:01:25.780 align:middle line:84%
really was an opportunity for
me to contribute to people

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:27.580 align:middle line:90%
that wanted to really know how.

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:29.950 align:middle line:10%
I think it's a time in
history where people just

00:01:29.950 --> 00:01:32.320 align:middle line:10%
don't want to know, but
they want to know how.

00:01:32.320 --> 00:01:34.370 align:middle line:10%
So the premise of the
book really is simple.

00:01:34.370 --> 00:01:38.860 align:middle line:10%
It says your personality
creates your personal reality.

00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:42.610 align:middle line:10%
And your personality is made up
of how you think, how you act,

00:01:42.610 --> 00:01:44.080 align:middle line:10%
and how you feel.

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:46.720 align:middle line:84%
So the present personality
sitting here today

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:50.710 align:middle line:84%
has created the present personal
reality called your life, which

00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:53.890 align:middle line:84%
also means that if you wanted to
create a new personal reality,

00:01:53.890 --> 00:01:55.690 align:middle line:84%
then on a fundamental
level, you would have

00:01:55.690 --> 00:02:00.770 align:middle line:84%
to change some thoughts,
begin to behave differently,

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:02.930 align:middle line:84%
and begin to live by
different emotions.

00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:05.140 align:middle line:84%
So I think the biggest
problem with all of us

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:08.020 align:middle line:84%
is that we try to create
a new personal reality

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:10.178 align:middle line:84%
as the same personality,
and it never works.

00:02:10.178 --> 00:02:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you said, the way
to change that personality

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:13.595 align:middle line:90%
is to change your thoughts.

00:02:13.595 --> 00:02:14.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Mm-hmm.

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:16.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Easier said than
done, and it's not just

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:17.110 align:middle line:90%
about the thoughts.

00:02:17.110 --> 00:02:17.500 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Mm-hmm.

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:19.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have to change your
entire physiology around it,

00:02:19.750 --> 00:02:20.140 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.220 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Absolutely.

00:02:21.220 --> 00:02:25.413 align:middle line:84%
So the key element to
change is to be greater

00:02:25.413 --> 00:02:27.580 align:middle line:84%
than your environment, to
be greater than your body,

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:28.750 align:middle line:90%
and to be greater than time.

00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And when we get about
the business of change,

00:02:32.110 --> 00:02:35.230 align:middle line:84%
we're always interacting
with the same people,

00:02:35.230 --> 00:02:37.720 align:middle line:84%
and doing the same things,
and going to the same places.

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:40.212 align:middle line:84%
And it's the environment,
our external world

00:02:40.212 --> 00:02:41.920 align:middle line:84%
that's controlling
how we think and feel.

00:02:41.920 --> 00:02:43.087 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Our patterns, right?

00:02:43.087 --> 00:02:45.760 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: The moment we
begin to react in the same way

00:02:45.760 --> 00:02:48.130 align:middle line:84%
to the same conditions
in our life,

00:02:48.130 --> 00:02:51.010 align:middle line:84%
then we begin to cause
different circuits in our brain

00:02:51.010 --> 00:02:54.160 align:middle line:84%
to turn on, equal to everything
that we know in our life.

00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:56.320 align:middle line:84%
And that repetition
over time begins

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:58.210 align:middle line:84%
to hard wire our
brain to everything

00:02:58.210 --> 00:02:59.230 align:middle line:90%
familiar in our life.

00:02:59.230 --> 00:03:00.813 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So give me
an example of that.

00:03:00.813 --> 00:03:03.140 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, you
wake up in the morning.

00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:05.200 align:middle line:90%
You go to work the same way.

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.625 align:middle line:84%
You see the same
people, that push

00:03:06.625 --> 00:03:07.750 align:middle line:90%
the same emotional buttons.

00:03:07.750 --> 00:03:09.850 align:middle line:84%
You get at your desk
and you do the things

00:03:09.850 --> 00:03:11.680 align:middle line:90%
that you know how to do so well.

00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:13.450 align:middle line:84%
You drink coffee out
of your favorite mug.

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:15.670 align:middle line:84%
You complain to the same
people in the same way, that

00:03:15.670 --> 00:03:17.550 align:middle line:90%
stir up the same emotions.

00:03:17.550 --> 00:03:20.050 align:middle line:84%
You see the same people that
push the same emotional buttons

00:03:20.050 --> 00:03:21.010 align:middle line:90%
with you.

00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And then, in time, we could say
that the environment, really,

00:03:25.030 --> 00:03:27.550 align:middle line:84%
is shaping and molding
how we think and feel.

00:03:27.550 --> 00:03:30.340 align:middle line:84%
So to change then is to be
greater than the environment,

00:03:30.340 --> 00:03:33.460 align:middle line:84%
to begin to act, and
think, and feel differently

00:03:33.460 --> 00:03:34.960 align:middle line:90%
than our present circumstances.

00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:37.480 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So it doesn't work
that you even just change

00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:41.290 align:middle line:10%
your routine, because you
will automatically set it up

00:03:41.290 --> 00:03:43.323 align:middle line:10%
to create the same
type of circumstances

00:03:43.323 --> 00:03:45.490 align:middle line:10%
with a whole different
routine-- if you change jobs,

00:03:45.490 --> 00:03:48.740 align:middle line:10%
if you take your child to
school, or whatever it is.

00:03:48.740 --> 00:03:49.540 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:51.790 align:middle line:84%
And there's a concept
in neuroscience

00:03:51.790 --> 00:03:53.530 align:middle line:90%
called neuroplasticity.

00:03:53.530 --> 00:03:55.210 align:middle line:84%
And plasticity
tells us that we're

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:57.040 align:middle line:84%
changed by every
thought we think,

00:03:57.040 --> 00:04:00.640 align:middle line:84%
every new experience we have,
every different choice we make,

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:02.530 align:middle line:84%
every new dream
that we fabricate.

00:04:02.530 --> 00:04:05.560 align:middle line:84%
The brain literally
reorganizes itself

00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:07.330 align:middle line:90%
to reflect a new level of mind.

00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:08.770 align:middle line:84%
Which begs the
question, I think,

00:04:08.770 --> 00:04:10.600 align:middle line:84%
that most people
really are thinking

00:04:10.600 --> 00:04:13.250 align:middle line:84%
the same way every day,
acting the same way,

00:04:13.250 --> 00:04:15.550 align:middle line:84%
and feeling the same way,
but really hoping something

00:04:15.550 --> 00:04:17.967 align:middle line:84%
will show up differently in
their life, and it never does.

00:04:17.967 --> 00:04:20.950 align:middle line:84%
So hard wiring our
brain over time

00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:22.750 align:middle line:84%
to the same
conditions in our life

00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:25.630 align:middle line:84%
then causes us to think
equal to everything we know.

00:04:25.630 --> 00:04:28.510 align:middle line:84%
And if we believe in any
way that our thoughts have

00:04:28.510 --> 00:04:30.640 align:middle line:84%
something to do with
our destiny, then

00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:33.460 align:middle line:84%
as long as we're reacting to
everything we know in our life,

00:04:33.460 --> 00:04:35.290 align:middle line:84%
we keep creating
more of the same.

00:04:35.290 --> 00:04:39.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So neuroplasticity is
the way that the brain actually

00:04:39.370 --> 00:04:40.320 align:middle line:90%
makes those changes.

00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:42.730 align:middle line:84%
It's the connections of
neurons, is that what it is?

00:04:42.730 --> 00:04:45.147 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah, they used
to say that your brain is hard

00:04:45.147 --> 00:04:47.800 align:middle line:84%
wired, and you're going to turn
out just like your parents,

00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:49.700 align:middle line:84%
and that you're
doomed by your genes,

00:04:49.700 --> 00:04:51.130 align:middle line:90%
and that's the end of your life.

00:04:51.130 --> 00:04:54.610 align:middle line:84%
But actually, we're marvels of
plasticity and adaptability.

00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:57.640 align:middle line:84%
And as long as you're
evolving your actions

00:04:57.640 --> 00:05:00.880 align:middle line:84%
and modifying your behaviors
to do a better job in life,

00:05:00.880 --> 00:05:03.220 align:middle line:84%
your brain literally
installs new circuitry

00:05:03.220 --> 00:05:05.590 align:middle line:90%
to reflect your own evolution.

00:05:05.590 --> 00:05:07.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so
that new circuitry

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:10.840 align:middle line:84%
comes, though, from our own
thoughts changing our brain,

00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:12.550 align:middle line:84%
or does it come from
the environment?

00:05:12.550 --> 00:05:14.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, I
think most people really

00:05:14.660 --> 00:05:18.920 align:middle line:84%
wait for trauma, or crisis,
or loss, or disease, tragedy

00:05:18.920 --> 00:05:19.730 align:middle line:90%
in some way.

00:05:19.730 --> 00:05:21.650 align:middle line:84%
And then when they
get to that point

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:24.200 align:middle line:84%
where we reach our
lowest denominator,

00:05:24.200 --> 00:05:26.990 align:middle line:84%
that's when we begin
to examine ourselves.

00:05:26.990 --> 00:05:30.560 align:middle line:84%
And that concept in neuroscience
is called meta cognition.

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.420 align:middle line:84%
And meta cognition says
that we can pay attention

00:05:33.420 --> 00:05:34.220 align:middle line:90%
to how we think.

00:05:34.220 --> 00:05:36.110 align:middle line:90%
We can notice how we feel.

00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:38.750 align:middle line:84%
We can become aware
of how we act.

00:05:38.750 --> 00:05:41.870 align:middle line:84%
So that those are in place so
we can modify our behaviors

00:05:41.870 --> 00:05:44.060 align:middle line:84%
to begin to produce
different outcomes.

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:47.520 align:middle line:84%
So plasticity gives us
that permission to do it.

00:05:47.520 --> 00:05:50.630 align:middle line:84%
But once again,
though, biology then

00:05:50.630 --> 00:05:53.050 align:middle line:84%
is a direct result
of consciousness.

00:05:53.050 --> 00:05:55.040 align:middle line:84%
So if you keep
everything the same,

00:05:55.040 --> 00:05:56.630 align:middle line:84%
then your biology
stays the same.

00:05:56.630 --> 00:05:59.270 align:middle line:84%
And now you're headed
for your genetic destiny.

00:05:59.270 --> 00:06:01.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So Dr.
Joe was in a movie

00:06:01.670 --> 00:06:04.530 align:middle line:84%
called "The People versus
the State of illusion."

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:08.150 align:middle line:10%
