00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And what was once very adaptive,
like if you were being chased

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:09.830 align:middle line:84%
by a lion thousands
of years ago,

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:13.340 align:middle line:84%
you'd have to mobilize a lot of
energy to either stay and fight

00:09:13.340 --> 00:09:14.630 align:middle line:90%
or to run.

00:09:14.630 --> 00:09:17.390 align:middle line:84%
Now it becomes more
complex in our society,

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:19.700 align:middle line:84%
because you could
see a co-worker,

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:21.550 align:middle line:84%
you could see your
mother-in-law--

00:09:21.550 --> 00:09:22.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You could
have a bad day.

00:09:22.490 --> 00:09:24.032 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You
could have a bad day.

00:09:24.032 --> 00:09:27.500 align:middle line:84%
You could begin to auto suggest
about problems in your life.

00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:29.300 align:middle line:84%
And the privilege of
being a human being

00:09:29.300 --> 00:09:32.130 align:middle line:84%
is that we can make thought
more real than anything else.

00:09:32.130 --> 00:09:35.450 align:middle line:84%
And when we do that, we begin
to turn on the stress response

00:09:35.450 --> 00:09:37.037 align:middle line:90%
just by thought alone.

00:09:37.037 --> 00:09:39.245 align:middle line:84%
And stress is when the body's
knocked out of balance.

00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:42.315 align:middle line:84%
The stress response is what the
body does to innately turn it

00:09:42.315 --> 00:09:43.115 align:middle line:90%
back to order.

00:09:43.115 --> 00:09:46.580 align:middle line:84%
The problem is if you keep
turning on that fight or flight

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:50.150 align:middle line:84%
nervous system, that imbalance
now becomes the new balance.

00:09:50.150 --> 00:09:51.560 align:middle line:84%
And now we're
headed for disease.

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:52.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Chronic, mm-hmm.

00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:54.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So the
stress in the brain

00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:57.650 align:middle line:84%
causes the forebrain, or
rational brain to turn off,

00:09:57.650 --> 00:10:00.950 align:middle line:84%
and the hindbrain to begin
to secrete all these juices.

00:10:00.950 --> 00:10:03.860 align:middle line:84%
So what was once very adaptive
thousands of years ago

00:10:03.860 --> 00:10:06.440 align:middle line:84%
becomes very
maladaptive, because it's

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:09.560 align:middle line:84%
those chemicals of stress that
push the genetic buttons that

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:11.010 align:middle line:90%
begin to create disease.

00:10:11.010 --> 00:10:14.720 align:middle line:84%
And if you think about this, we
can turn on the stress response

00:10:14.720 --> 00:10:16.220 align:middle line:90%
just by thought alone.

00:10:16.220 --> 00:10:19.460 align:middle line:84%
Then by very nature, our
thoughts can make us sick.

00:10:19.460 --> 00:10:20.960 align:middle line:84%
So if our thoughts
can make us sick,

00:10:20.960 --> 00:10:23.370 align:middle line:84%
is it possible that our
thoughts could make us well?

00:10:23.370 --> 00:10:25.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a clip that
shows this, that really shows

00:10:25.820 --> 00:10:28.190 align:middle line:84%
the entire fight or flight
response in the body,

00:10:28.190 --> 00:10:29.463 align:middle line:90%
that we have here.

00:10:29.463 --> 00:10:31.130 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a
little bit about this?

00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:33.140 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Sure, we
were just talking about--

00:10:33.140 --> 00:10:35.598 align:middle line:84%
you see a lion in
the Serengeti, you're

00:10:35.598 --> 00:10:37.640 align:middle line:84%
going to turn on a very
primitive nervous system.

00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:38.780 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't
have to be a lion,

00:10:38.780 --> 00:10:40.488 align:middle line:84%
it could be your
mother-in-law and you'll

00:10:40.488 --> 00:10:41.570 align:middle line:90%
have the same reaction.

00:10:41.570 --> 00:10:44.660 align:middle line:84%
Or you can begin to think
my bills are overdue,

00:10:44.660 --> 00:10:47.390 align:middle line:84%
rent is overdue, I
have problems at work.

00:10:47.390 --> 00:10:50.660 align:middle line:84%
And just by you thinking
about your problems,

00:10:50.660 --> 00:10:54.770 align:middle line:84%
you begin to turn on the same
reaction in your brain and body

00:10:54.770 --> 00:10:57.200 align:middle line:84%
as if you were being
chased by a lion.

00:10:57.200 --> 00:11:00.200 align:middle line:84%
And that effect, then, that
begins to knock the body out

00:11:00.200 --> 00:11:03.440 align:middle line:84%
of balance, begins to turn on
this primitive nervous system

00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:06.920 align:middle line:84%
that begins to secrete a lot
of adrenaline and cortisol.

00:11:06.920 --> 00:11:09.200 align:middle line:84%
And those chemicals,
those stress hormones,

00:11:09.200 --> 00:11:11.120 align:middle line:90%
give the body a rush of energy.

00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:13.820 align:middle line:84%
You're prepared for an
emergency situation.

00:11:13.820 --> 00:11:15.920 align:middle line:90%
So your pupils dilate.

00:11:15.920 --> 00:11:19.910 align:middle line:84%
Then your salivary juices
begin to slow down.

00:11:19.910 --> 00:11:22.280 align:middle line:84%
You start to get more blood
pumping into your body.

00:11:22.280 --> 00:11:25.197 align:middle line:84%
Your heart rate and respiratory
rate begin to increase.

00:11:25.197 --> 00:11:26.780 align:middle line:84%
And blood is sent
to your extremities.

00:11:26.780 --> 00:11:29.720 align:middle line:84%
And you're prepared for
an emergency situation.

00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:31.670 align:middle line:84%
Now you're ready to
either fight or run.

00:11:31.670 --> 00:11:33.450 align:middle line:90%
So it's all great.

00:11:33.450 --> 00:11:36.170 align:middle line:84%
The problem is is that
if you're confronting

00:11:36.170 --> 00:11:39.442 align:middle line:84%
the same person in your life,
you're going to the same job,

00:11:39.442 --> 00:11:41.150 align:middle line:84%
and you're seeing the
same co-worker that

00:11:41.150 --> 00:11:43.160 align:middle line:84%
pushes the same
emotional button,

00:11:43.160 --> 00:11:45.680 align:middle line:84%
that in time then,
you're subconsciously

00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:48.710 align:middle line:84%
or unconsciously knocking your
brain and body out of balance.

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:52.310 align:middle line:84%
And the long-term effects
then begin to create disease.

00:11:52.310 --> 00:11:54.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can the body
become then addicted

00:11:54.260 --> 00:11:57.610 align:middle line:84%
to the adrenaline rush
that comes from those fight

00:11:57.610 --> 00:11:58.670 align:middle line:90%
or flight situations?

00:11:58.670 --> 00:11:59.300 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Absolutely.

00:11:59.300 --> 00:12:00.967 align:middle line:84%
If you think about
it, if you're getting

00:12:00.967 --> 00:12:02.960 align:middle line:84%
a rush of energy, a
rush of adrenaline,

00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:04.940 align:middle line:90%
that's like a triple cappuccino.

00:12:04.940 --> 00:12:07.610 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, you get this
heightened sense of awareness.

00:12:07.610 --> 00:12:10.620 align:middle line:84%
The brain and the body
wake up momentarily.

00:12:10.620 --> 00:12:14.630 align:middle line:84%
Now that only should
last for about 90 seconds

00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:15.470 align:middle line:90%
to two minutes.

00:12:15.470 --> 00:12:17.450 align:middle line:84%
And I tell my
children all the time,

00:12:17.450 --> 00:12:20.690 align:middle line:84%
if you're angry for more than
two minutes, you're faking it.

00:12:20.690 --> 00:12:23.360 align:middle line:84%
In other words, when the
stress response happens,

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:25.400 align:middle line:90%
we should be able to control it.

00:12:25.400 --> 00:12:28.730 align:middle line:84%
A good example of an addiction
is something you can't stop.

00:12:28.730 --> 00:12:31.290 align:middle line:84%
So if you were in the midst
of say an angry reaction

00:12:31.290 --> 00:12:33.290 align:middle line:84%
to something in your life,
and I came up to you,

00:12:33.290 --> 00:12:37.040 align:middle line:84%
and I said, Lisa, listen, I
know you're angry, but why

00:12:37.040 --> 00:12:38.570 align:middle line:90%
don't you just stop right now?

00:12:38.570 --> 00:12:40.370 align:middle line:84%
Most people would say,
are you kidding me?

00:12:40.370 --> 00:12:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:43.218 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: It's because of
this situation and this person.

00:12:43.218 --> 00:12:46.050 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say, yeah, yeah, I
know, but just stop that.

00:12:46.050 --> 00:12:49.220 align:middle line:84%
So if you're unable to stop
the emotional reaction,

00:12:49.220 --> 00:12:51.050 align:middle line:84%
then that's the definition
of an addiction.

00:12:51.050 --> 00:12:55.100 align:middle line:84%
So these chemicals
really are highly charged

00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:56.780 align:middle line:90%
energetic signatures.

00:12:56.780 --> 00:12:58.640 align:middle line:84%
And they create the
emotional states

00:12:58.640 --> 00:13:02.840 align:middle line:84%
of anger, and aggression, and
hatred, and judgment, and fear,

00:13:02.840 --> 00:13:05.990 align:middle line:84%
and anxiety, and hopelessness,
and powerlessness,

00:13:05.990 --> 00:13:07.460 align:middle line:90%
and depression.

00:13:07.460 --> 00:13:10.280 align:middle line:84%
Those chemicals knock
the body out of balance.

00:13:10.280 --> 00:13:13.910 align:middle line:84%
And we begin to call those
altered states of consciousness

00:13:13.910 --> 00:13:15.230 align:middle line:90%
normal states of consciousness.

00:13:15.230 --> 00:13:17.210 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, they're
really causing

00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:19.790 align:middle line:84%
us to live as
primitive human beings.

00:13:19.790 --> 00:13:21.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then they
turn into habits.

00:13:21.420 --> 00:13:25.035 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Right, because
as the emotion begins to run,

00:13:25.035 --> 00:13:26.660 align:middle line:84%
the chemicals that
run through the body

00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:29.210 align:middle line:84%
begin to signal the very
thoughts that we think.

00:13:29.210 --> 00:13:32.650 align:middle line:84%
And when we're in the midst
of an emotional reaction

00:13:32.650 --> 00:13:35.150 align:middle line:84%
to something or
someone in our life,

00:13:35.150 --> 00:13:38.760 align:middle line:84%
there's always a gap between the
way things appear and the way

00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:39.790 align:middle line:90%
things really are.

00:13:39.790 --> 00:13:41.580 align:middle line:84%
The chemicals alter
our perception.

00:13:41.580 --> 00:13:44.520 align:middle line:84%
And if we react during
the refractory period

00:13:44.520 --> 00:13:46.890 align:middle line:84%
of those chemicals,
we'll always say,

00:13:46.890 --> 00:13:48.150 align:middle line:90%
I should've never said that.

00:13:48.150 --> 00:13:49.380 align:middle line:84%
I should have
never thought that.

00:13:49.380 --> 00:13:50.650 align:middle line:90%
I should have never done that.

00:13:50.650 --> 00:13:54.968 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But I mean, if somebody
did something that was wrong,

00:13:54.968 --> 00:13:57.510 align:middle line:84%
and I get upset over it, are
you telling me not to get upset?

00:13:57.510 --> 00:14:00.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: No, no, I'm saying
that emotions are part of life.

00:14:00.540 --> 00:14:03.180 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing wrong with
having an emotional reaction.

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:07.110 align:middle line:84%
The question is, how long the
refractory period of chemicals

00:14:07.110 --> 00:14:08.000 align:middle line:90%
run.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:10.980 align:middle line:84%
And if you keep an emotional
reaction running for hours

00:14:10.980 --> 00:14:12.360 align:middle line:90%
or days, that's called a mood.

00:14:12.360 --> 00:14:14.940 align:middle line:84%
And if you ask a person,
why are you in this mood,

00:14:14.940 --> 00:14:17.737 align:middle line:84%
they'll tell you because
something happened 10 days ago.

00:14:17.737 --> 00:14:19.320 align:middle line:84%
And if you keep that
refractory period

00:14:19.320 --> 00:14:21.725 align:middle line:84%
going for weeks or months,
that's called a temperament.

00:14:21.725 --> 00:14:24.100 align:middle line:84%
And you'd say, why do you have
such an angry temperament.

00:14:24.100 --> 00:14:25.710 align:middle line:84%
And that person
would say something

00:14:25.710 --> 00:14:27.428 align:middle line:90%
happened to me 10 months ago.

00:14:27.428 --> 00:14:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And if you keep the refractory
period going for years on end,

00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:31.860 align:middle line:84%
that's called a
personality trait.

00:14:31.860 --> 00:14:35.100 align:middle line:84%
And so if we wanted to change
some aspect of our personality,

00:14:35.100 --> 00:14:37.800 align:middle line:84%
we have to look at the
emotions, layer by layer,

00:14:37.800 --> 00:14:40.950 align:middle line:84%
that we memorize, that's
become part of our identity.

00:14:40.950 --> 00:14:43.890 align:middle line:84%
And if emotions are
the record of the past,

00:14:43.890 --> 00:14:46.438 align:middle line:84%
and you're living by the
same emotion every day,

00:14:46.438 --> 00:14:47.730 align:middle line:90%
then you're living in the past.

00:14:47.730 --> 00:14:49.950 align:middle line:84%
And your body as
the unconscious mind

00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:52.740 align:middle line:84%
is believing that it's
in the same circumstances

00:14:52.740 --> 00:14:53.540 align:middle line:90%
24 hours a day--

00:14:53.540 --> 00:14:54.582 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Moment by moment.

00:14:54.582 --> 00:14:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: --seven days
a week, 365 days a year.

00:14:56.800 --> 00:15:00.303 align:middle line:84%
And that body can't take the
redundancy of those chemicals.

00:15:00.303 --> 00:15:01.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's when it
begins to break down.

00:15:01.970 --> 00:15:05.340 align:middle line:84%
Just like being in the presence
of a lion, in the same cage

00:15:05.340 --> 00:15:06.215 align:middle line:90%
with a lion day long.

00:15:06.215 --> 00:15:07.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All the time.

00:15:07.090 --> 00:15:08.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So emotional
intelligence, then,

00:15:08.940 --> 00:15:11.290 align:middle line:84%
is learning how to shorten
that refractory period.

00:15:11.290 --> 00:15:14.370 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to shorten
that refractory period,

00:15:14.370 --> 00:15:15.960 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't create your identity.

00:15:15.960 --> 00:15:17.640 align:middle line:84%
You get to say,
just like a child,

00:15:17.640 --> 00:15:19.650 align:middle line:84%
you move through the
emotion, you get rid of it.

00:15:19.650 --> 00:15:21.690 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't filter
your perception

00:15:21.690 --> 00:15:24.640 align:middle line:84%
for the rest of your day or
for the rest of your life.

00:15:24.640 --> 00:15:27.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is what
resilience is essentially.

00:15:27.100 --> 00:15:28.850 align:middle line:84%
So we have some clips
that I talked to you

00:15:28.850 --> 00:15:33.660 align:middle line:84%
about that are actual slides of
what the neurons in the brain

00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:36.980 align:middle line:84%
look like when they create
new responses to things,

00:15:36.980 --> 00:15:37.900 align:middle line:90%
new memories, right?

00:15:37.900 --> 00:15:40.400 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Sure, we'll talk
about primarily-- the first two

00:15:40.400 --> 00:15:43.050 align:middle line:84%
clips show how we have
neurons actually connecting

00:15:43.050 --> 00:15:45.030 align:middle line:84%
and hard wiring into
certain patterns.

00:15:45.030 --> 00:15:46.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK so this could
be a negative pattern or--

00:15:46.650 --> 00:15:47.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: It could
be a negative pattern

00:15:47.210 --> 00:15:48.800 align:middle line:90%
or a positive pattern.

00:15:48.800 --> 00:15:51.870 align:middle line:84%
If you have good habits, and
you have things about yourself

00:15:51.870 --> 00:15:54.390 align:middle line:84%
that you like, and
you do certain things

00:15:54.390 --> 00:15:57.510 align:middle line:84%
that you have become
skilled at, well, that's

00:15:57.510 --> 00:16:00.210 align:middle line:84%
a good hardwired pattern
that you want to maintain.

00:16:00.210 --> 00:16:01.770 align:middle line:84%
But if you have
some habits that are

00:16:01.770 --> 00:16:04.140 align:middle line:84%
self-destructive
or self-limiting,

00:16:04.140 --> 00:16:06.900 align:middle line:84%
those are fired and wired
by your own volition.

00:16:06.900 --> 00:16:10.680 align:middle line:84%
Now the principal says that
if you stop thinking, acting,

00:16:10.680 --> 00:16:13.020 align:middle line:84%
and feeling the
same way, the nerve

00:16:13.020 --> 00:16:15.330 align:middle line:84%
cells that no longer
fire together no

00:16:15.330 --> 00:16:16.320 align:middle line:90%
longer wire together.

00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:19.500 align:middle line:84%
As you stop communicating
neurologically, just

00:16:19.500 --> 00:16:21.880 align:middle line:84%
like any relationship,
you begin to break apart

00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:22.680 align:middle line:90%
those connections.

00:16:22.680 --> 00:16:24.472 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you have a
thought in the brain.

00:16:24.472 --> 00:16:26.040 align:middle line:90%
This is what it looks like.

00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:26.927 align:middle line:90%
Or is this a memory?

00:16:26.927 --> 00:16:28.260 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: So this is a memory.

00:16:28.260 --> 00:16:30.720 align:middle line:84%
When two neurons have
fired and wired together,

00:16:30.720 --> 00:16:32.670 align:middle line:84%
they have a lasting
relationship that

00:16:32.670 --> 00:16:35.580 align:middle line:84%
can be related to any thought,
skill, behavior, concept,

00:16:35.580 --> 00:16:37.500 align:middle line:90%
or some idea.

00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:39.437 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so they
create a synapse together.

00:16:39.437 --> 00:16:41.520 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: They develop
a long-term relationship.

00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:45.240 align:middle line:84%
And those connections facilitate
a stream of consciousness.

00:16:45.240 --> 00:16:47.250 align:middle line:90%
They facilitate a level of mind.

00:16:47.250 --> 00:16:49.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's
another slide here.

00:16:49.380 --> 00:16:51.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So this is
another hardwired neuron.

00:16:51.380 --> 00:16:52.850 align:middle line:84%
They're in a long-term
relationship.

00:16:52.850 --> 00:16:53.650 align:middle line:90%
This could be fear.

00:16:53.650 --> 00:16:55.110 align:middle line:90%
It could be joy.

00:16:55.110 --> 00:16:56.550 align:middle line:90%
It could be brushing your teeth.

00:16:56.550 --> 00:16:59.190 align:middle line:84%
Those neurons now have
been used enough times

00:16:59.190 --> 00:17:01.420 align:middle line:84%
that they're mapped
neurologically in the brain.

00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:03.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So they create a
bridge, essentially a chain.

00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:04.553 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Exactly.

00:17:04.553 --> 00:17:09.480 align:middle line:84%
If you look at this slide here,
this slide represents learning.

00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:11.640 align:middle line:84%
Every time you
learn something new

00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:14.319 align:middle line:84%
you make a new synaptic
connection in your brain.

00:17:14.319 --> 00:17:17.369 align:middle line:84%
So as you pay attention and
you begin to become present

00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:19.530 align:middle line:84%
in the moment, your
brain literally up

00:17:19.530 --> 00:17:22.230 align:middle line:84%
scales its hardware to
reflect the new level of mind.

00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:23.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is amazing.

00:17:23.230 --> 00:17:24.630 align:middle line:90%
It's like it reaches--

00:17:24.630 --> 00:17:26.680 align:middle line:84%
it's almost as if it's
reaching for the new--

00:17:26.680 --> 00:17:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: There's
an intelligence there.

00:17:28.430 --> 00:17:30.660 align:middle line:84%
And so, it's amazing,
because we reach

00:17:30.660 --> 00:17:34.500 align:middle line:84%
a certain point in our life, I
think, where we stop learning

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:36.170 align:middle line:90%
and we start feeling.

00:17:36.170 --> 00:17:40.155 align:middle line:84%
And when we do that, we trade
off our own personal evolution.

00:17:40.155 --> 00:17:41.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What do
you mean by that?

00:17:41.530 --> 00:17:43.350 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, we get
to a point in our life

00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:45.780 align:middle line:84%
where we pretty much can
predict the feeling of anything.

00:17:45.780 --> 00:17:48.420 align:middle line:84%
You get to be about
35 or 40 years old,

00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:51.330 align:middle line:84%
psychology tells us that
the personality's usually

00:17:51.330 --> 00:17:52.380 align:middle line:90%
complete at that point.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:54.240 align:middle line:90%
And in some degree, that's true.

00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:56.280 align:middle line:84%
And so people experience
relationships,

00:17:56.280 --> 00:17:57.720 align:middle line:90%
they experience sexuality.

00:17:57.720 --> 00:18:01.020 align:middle line:84%
They experience their
successes and their failures,

00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:04.590 align:middle line:84%
their importance, and their
unworthiness, and their guilt.

00:18:04.590 --> 00:18:07.720 align:middle line:84%
And they pretty much experience
much of what life has to offer.

00:18:07.720 --> 00:18:10.740 align:middle line:84%
So when you can predict
the feeling of anything,

00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:13.370 align:middle line:84%
well how can anything
new show up in your life,

00:18:13.370 --> 00:18:16.470 align:middle line:84%
because by very definition,
you're forecasting your future

00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:17.940 align:middle line:90%
based on your past.

00:18:17.940 --> 00:18:19.530 align:middle line:84%
We've reached this
point where we're

00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:22.670 align:middle line:84%
using feelings as a
barometer to determine life.

00:18:22.670 --> 00:18:24.030 align:middle line:90%
We'll always miss adventure.

00:18:24.030 --> 00:18:25.500 align:middle line:90%
We'll always miss opportunities.

00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:29.100 align:middle line:84%
So when we begin to
continue to learn, continue

00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:32.370 align:middle line:84%
to evolve our actions, continue
to experience new things,

00:18:32.370 --> 00:18:35.970 align:middle line:84%
continue to step outside the
box and try something else out,

00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:38.170 align:middle line:84%
you're going to shake up
neurologically your own sub

00:18:38.170 --> 00:18:39.060 align:middle line:90%
structures in your brain.

00:18:39.060 --> 00:18:39.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love that.

00:18:39.690 --> 00:18:40.490 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:18:40.490 --> 00:18:43.500 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a pattern
that you would like to break,

00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:46.180 align:middle line:84%
by introducing new thoughts--and
we're going to get into that--

00:18:46.180 --> 00:18:48.388 align:middle line:84%
but this is what it actually
looks like in the brain.

00:18:48.388 --> 00:18:50.670 align:middle line:10%
>>DISPENZA: The
first stage anytime

00:18:50.670 --> 00:18:53.550 align:middle line:10%
is that you have to begin
to assemble a new mind.

00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:57.870 align:middle line:84%
So if you wanted to become a
more loving parent or a more

00:18:57.870 --> 00:19:00.390 align:middle line:84%
patient parent, or if
you wanted to become

00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:03.480 align:middle line:84%
a more successful businesswoman
or a more successful

00:19:03.480 --> 00:19:06.025 align:middle line:84%
entrepreneur, the first thing
you're going to have to do

00:19:06.025 --> 00:19:07.650 align:middle line:84%
is you're going to
have to start asking

00:19:07.650 --> 00:19:11.490 align:middle line:84%
some important questions, like
what is it to be successful?

00:19:11.490 --> 00:19:14.062 align:middle line:84%
What do I have to change
about myself to be wealthy?

00:19:14.062 --> 00:19:15.520 align:middle line:84%
What does a great
parent look like?

00:19:15.520 --> 00:19:17.388 align:middle line:84%
Who in history was
great that I admire?

00:19:17.388 --> 00:19:18.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And how did they think?

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:20.138 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And
how did they think?

00:19:20.138 --> 00:19:22.890 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to
read this information,

00:19:22.890 --> 00:19:24.990 align:middle line:84%
you're installing new
circuits in your brain.

00:19:24.990 --> 00:19:27.600 align:middle line:84%
But you better review
that information

00:19:27.600 --> 00:19:30.420 align:middle line:84%
because it takes a
series of repetitions

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:33.000 align:middle line:84%
before you begin to
create networks of neurons

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:35.430 align:middle line:84%
that will literally
become the forerunner

00:19:35.430 --> 00:19:36.670 align:middle line:90%
to the next experience.

00:19:36.670 --> 00:19:39.210 align:middle line:84%
So now, when you learn that
knowledge, and you apply it,

00:19:39.210 --> 00:19:41.550 align:middle line:84%
and you personalize it,
and you demonstrate it,

00:19:41.550 --> 00:19:43.715 align:middle line:84%
you're going to modify
your behavior in some way.

00:19:43.715 --> 00:19:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And when you change
your actions,

00:19:45.090 --> 00:19:46.673 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
a new experience.

00:19:46.673 --> 00:19:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Now experience is
going to really enrich

00:19:48.390 --> 00:19:50.220 align:middle line:84%
the brain, because
jungles of neurons

00:19:50.220 --> 00:19:53.085 align:middle line:84%
are going to begin to organize
to reinforce the circuits

00:19:53.085 --> 00:19:54.210 align:middle line:90%
you learned intellectually.

00:19:54.210 --> 00:19:57.320 align:middle line:84%
The moment that happens, the
experience produces an emotion.

00:19:57.320 --> 00:20:00.810 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you feel success,
the moment you feel compassion,

00:20:00.810 --> 00:20:03.100 align:middle line:84%
the moment you feel
like a great parent, now

00:20:03.100 --> 00:20:06.090 align:middle line:84%
you're instructing and
teaching your body chemically

00:20:06.090 --> 00:20:08.010 align:middle line:84%
what your mind has
intellectually understood.

00:20:08.010 --> 00:20:10.110 align:middle line:84%
So you could say knowledge
is for the brain,

00:20:10.110 --> 00:20:12.120 align:middle line:90%
but experiences is for the body.

00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:13.080 align:middle line:90%
Change looks like this.

00:20:13.080 --> 00:20:15.330 align:middle line:84%
Most people sit on the couch
with the remote control.

00:20:15.330 --> 00:20:17.310 align:middle line:90%
They got their laptop over here.

00:20:17.310 --> 00:20:19.562 align:middle line:90%
They got their smartphone here.

00:20:19.562 --> 00:20:21.270 align:middle line:84%
They got the television
in front of them.

00:20:21.270 --> 00:20:26.310 align:middle line:84%
And they say, oh, I think
I'm going to change tomorrow.

00:20:26.310 --> 00:20:29.040 align:middle line:84%
Now, what do you think the
body, as the unconscious mind,

00:20:29.040 --> 00:20:29.460 align:middle line:90%
is going to say?

00:20:29.460 --> 00:20:31.200 align:middle line:84%
What you think the body as the
mind reader is going to say?

00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:31.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, it's not.

00:20:31.750 --> 00:20:33.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: No, relax,
you're not going to change.

00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:37.560 align:middle line:84%
But when you say, listen,
I don't care how I feel--

00:20:37.560 --> 00:20:40.470 align:middle line:84%
body, I don't care how
long it takes-- time.

00:20:40.470 --> 00:20:42.960 align:middle line:84%
I don't care what's going
on in my life-- environment.

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:43.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do this.

00:20:43.980 --> 00:20:46.170 align:middle line:84%
And the hair on the back
of your neck stands up.

00:20:46.170 --> 00:20:50.220 align:middle line:84%
The body gets a very strong
signal, which means, uh-oh,

00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:51.220 align:middle line:90%
she's serious this time.

00:20:51.220 --> 00:20:52.428 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's an aha moment.

00:20:52.428 --> 00:20:54.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: It's a moment
where the body gets--

00:20:54.390 --> 00:20:57.000 align:middle line:84%
the decision is
an experience that

00:20:57.000 --> 00:20:58.620 align:middle line:90%
begins to rewrite the program.

00:20:58.620 --> 00:21:03.390 align:middle line:84%
So that being said, there's
no actual amount of time

00:21:03.390 --> 00:21:04.980 align:middle line:84%
that it takes the
change a habit.

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:06.810 align:middle line:90%
Some people can do it overnight.

00:21:06.810 --> 00:21:08.430 align:middle line:84%
Some people can
make the decision,

00:21:08.430 --> 00:21:11.040 align:middle line:84%
and the message reaches
the body electrochemically,

00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:12.240 align:middle line:90%
and the person has done.

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:14.280 align:middle line:84%
Other people have
to pay attention.

00:21:14.280 --> 00:21:18.010 align:middle line:84%
They have to really
repeat it enough times.

00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:20.670 align:middle line:84%
There's a length of time
that they're actually putting

00:21:20.670 --> 00:21:21.865 align:middle line:90%
their attention behind it.

00:21:21.865 --> 00:21:22.990 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of variables.

00:21:22.990 --> 00:21:25.350 align:middle line:84%
But the key ingredient
is inspiration.

00:21:25.350 --> 00:21:27.760 align:middle line:84%
Because when you come out
of your resting state,

00:21:27.760 --> 00:21:30.720 align:middle line:84%
the body is the servant to
the mind, it's the animal.

00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:33.660 align:middle line:84%
And just like when you're
training an unbridled horse,

00:21:33.660 --> 00:21:35.520 align:middle line:84%
when you get ready
to ride that horse,

00:21:35.520 --> 00:21:38.770 align:middle line:84%
and you pull the reins in,
and you give it a good kick,

00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:41.067 align:middle line:84%
the horse says, OK, the
rider's ready this time.

00:21:41.067 --> 00:21:42.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's serious, yes.

00:21:42.150 --> 00:21:45.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And if you've
been away from the horse,

00:21:45.170 --> 00:21:47.340 align:middle line:84%
and you climb on that horse,
and you're not ready--

00:21:47.340 --> 00:21:47.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: They'll know.

00:21:47.550 --> 00:21:49.267 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: The
horse is the mind.

00:21:49.267 --> 00:21:50.850 align:middle line:84%
They did a scientific
experiment where

00:21:50.850 --> 00:21:52.500 align:middle line:84%
they took a group
of children that

00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:54.090 align:middle line:90%
scored poorly in mathematics.

00:21:54.090 --> 00:21:57.450 align:middle line:84%
And they taught them study
habits, and time management,

00:21:57.450 --> 00:21:58.890 align:middle line:90%
and outlining, and review.

00:21:58.890 --> 00:22:01.170 align:middle line:84%
And they gave them a
test three months later.

00:22:01.170 --> 00:22:02.820 align:middle line:84%
And these children
scored basically

00:22:02.820 --> 00:22:04.632 align:middle line:90%
the same or slightly higher.

00:22:04.632 --> 00:22:06.090 align:middle line:84%
They took another
group of children

00:22:06.090 --> 00:22:08.257 align:middle line:84%
and they taught them a short
course in neuroscience.

00:22:08.257 --> 00:22:10.470 align:middle line:84%
They showed them pictures
of neurons changing,

00:22:10.470 --> 00:22:11.712 align:middle line:90%
how the brain works.

00:22:11.712 --> 00:22:13.170 align:middle line:84%
And when they took
their test, they

00:22:13.170 --> 00:22:16.540 align:middle line:84%
scored way higher, because they
understood what they were doing

00:22:16.540 --> 00:22:17.340 align:middle line:90%
and why.

00:22:17.340 --> 00:22:19.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what I was
saying earlier, that these

00:22:19.590 --> 00:22:21.130 align:middle line:90%
