feeling that I have to be in
two places at the same time.

00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:19.890 align:middle line:84%
And if I then can change the
programming in my mind and make

00:26:19.890 --> 00:26:24.120 align:middle line:84%
the decision that I move through
my day with ease and grace--

00:26:24.120 --> 00:26:26.370 align:middle line:84%
I move through my day
with ease and grace,

00:26:26.370 --> 00:26:27.930 align:middle line:84%
then things and
people will start

00:26:27.930 --> 00:26:30.363 align:middle line:90%
to align around that, really?

00:26:30.363 --> 00:26:32.280 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, you
have to start to wire it

00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:33.060 align:middle line:90%
in your brain--

00:26:33.060 --> 00:26:33.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:26:33.860 --> 00:26:36.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Until you start to
actually accept the thought,

00:26:36.610 --> 00:26:37.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:26:37.410 --> 00:26:39.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: It means it's got
to make it past the brain stem

00:26:39.480 --> 00:26:40.650 align:middle line:90%
and start to stimulate the mind.

00:26:40.650 --> 00:26:41.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And all the
judgment, and the filters,

00:26:41.910 --> 00:26:44.100 align:middle line:84%
and the fast programming,
like we saw in the neurons.

00:26:44.100 --> 00:26:46.470 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Because if you can't
get beyond the analytical mind,

00:26:46.470 --> 00:26:48.720 align:middle line:84%
you never enter into the
operating system where

00:26:48.720 --> 00:26:49.950 align:middle line:90%
the change has to take place.

