00:27:10.680 --> 00:27:12.880 align:middle line:90%
taking place in your body.

00:27:12.880 --> 00:27:15.930 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to feel like
what that would feel like,

00:27:15.930 --> 00:27:18.690 align:middle line:84%
when mind and body
are working together,

00:27:18.690 --> 00:27:21.150 align:middle line:84%
now you get up in
a state of being.

00:27:21.150 --> 00:27:23.460 align:middle line:84%
Because a state of being is
when thoughts and feelings

00:27:23.460 --> 00:27:24.580 align:middle line:90%
are aligned.

00:27:24.580 --> 00:27:28.950 align:middle line:84%
Now you have to practice that
enough times so that it begins

00:27:28.950 --> 00:27:30.480 align:middle line:90%
to become familiar to you.

00:27:30.480 --> 00:27:32.310 align:middle line:84%
But if you did
this, and you said,

00:27:32.310 --> 00:27:36.760 align:middle line:84%
OK, universal mind, quantum
field, giver of life,

00:27:36.760 --> 00:27:39.930 align:middle line:84%
I took time out of my day
to emulate you as a creator.

00:27:39.930 --> 00:27:42.810 align:middle line:84%
So listen, if I'm
just a child of God,

00:27:42.810 --> 00:27:45.640 align:middle line:84%
and I'm practicing
this and experimenting,

00:27:45.640 --> 00:27:47.280 align:middle line:90%
I got to know that you're real.

00:27:47.280 --> 00:27:50.520 align:middle line:84%
So listen, if you've been
paying attention to my efforts,

00:27:50.520 --> 00:27:51.510 align:middle line:90%
show me a sign.

00:27:51.510 --> 00:27:53.670 align:middle line:84%
But don't show me
a typical sign.

00:27:53.670 --> 00:27:56.070 align:middle line:84%
Show me a sign
that I could never

00:27:56.070 --> 00:27:59.130 align:middle line:84%
predict, that surprises
me, that leaves no doubt

00:27:59.130 --> 00:28:01.440 align:middle line:84%
that what I did
inside of me produced

00:28:01.440 --> 00:28:03.330 align:middle line:84%
some result outside
of me, so that I'm

00:28:03.330 --> 00:28:04.747 align:middle line:90%
inspired to do it again.

00:28:04.747 --> 00:28:07.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now this is the
slide of what neuroplasticity

00:28:07.080 --> 00:28:08.130 align:middle line:90%
looks like in the brain.

00:28:08.130 --> 00:28:11.520 align:middle line:84%
The firings that you see are
electrical impulses happening.

00:28:11.520 --> 00:28:12.870 align:middle line:90%
And this is as we think.

00:28:12.870 --> 00:28:14.940 align:middle line:84%
How many times a
day does this occur?

00:28:14.940 --> 00:28:18.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: When you're in
your analytical critical self,

00:28:18.170 --> 00:28:20.460 align:middle line:84%
and you're in a certain
level of awareness,

00:28:20.460 --> 00:28:22.320 align:middle line:84%
your brain has to
create meaning between

00:28:22.320 --> 00:28:24.670 align:middle line:84%
the external environment and
the internal environment.

00:28:24.670 --> 00:28:26.045 align:middle line:84%
That's the function
of the brain.

00:28:26.045 --> 00:28:28.020 align:middle line:84%
So it's gathering all
this data and trying

00:28:28.020 --> 00:28:29.350 align:middle line:90%
to make meaning out of it.

00:28:29.350 --> 00:28:31.000 align:middle line:84%
But when you begin
to pay attention,

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:33.250 align:middle line:84%
and you begin to
focus and concentrate,

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:35.950 align:middle line:84%
the frontal lobe acts
like a volume control.

00:28:35.950 --> 00:28:37.450 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't want
to be distracted

00:28:37.450 --> 00:28:39.320 align:middle line:90%
by any extraneous stimuli.

00:28:39.320 --> 00:28:41.950 align:middle line:84%
So it begins to quiet down the
motor circuits in the brain

00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:43.110 align:middle line:90%
and you become still.

00:28:43.110 --> 00:28:44.770 align:middle line:84%
It cools off the
sensory circuits,

00:28:44.770 --> 00:28:46.240 align:middle line:84%
and you no longer
feel your body.

00:28:46.240 --> 00:28:48.340 align:middle line:84%
It cools off the
circuits in your brain

00:28:48.340 --> 00:28:50.440 align:middle line:90%
that process is time and space.

00:28:50.440 --> 00:28:53.410 align:middle line:10%
It even shuts out the
lights in the visual cortex

00:28:53.410 --> 00:28:54.550 align:middle line:10%
of your brain.

00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:58.030 align:middle line:10%
And it cools off the
mind-brain activity

00:28:58.030 --> 00:28:59.380 align:middle line:10%
in your association centers.

00:28:59.380 --> 00:29:00.430 align:middle line:10%
Now why does this happen?

00:29:00.430 --> 00:29:02.650 align:middle line:10%
Because when you're
able to quiet down

00:29:02.650 --> 00:29:05.680 align:middle line:10%
the circuits in your brain that
are reflected to everything

00:29:05.680 --> 00:29:07.810 align:middle line:10%
you know in your
life, the thought

00:29:07.810 --> 00:29:09.740 align:middle line:10%
that you're thinking
in that moment

00:29:09.740 --> 00:29:12.570 align:middle line:10%
literally becomes
the experience.

00:29:12.570 --> 00:29:14.500 align:middle line:84%
The thought becomes
the experience.

00:29:14.500 --> 00:29:17.320 align:middle line:84%
The brain upscales its
hardware to reflect the thought

00:29:17.320 --> 00:29:18.610 align:middle line:90%
as the experience.

00:29:18.610 --> 00:29:21.850 align:middle line:84%
So when the frontal lobe
is paying attention,

00:29:21.850 --> 00:29:24.790 align:middle line:84%
and you're truly in
a moment of presence,

00:29:24.790 --> 00:29:27.010 align:middle line:84%
your brain doesn't want to
be distracted by anything.

00:29:27.010 --> 00:29:29.140 align:middle line:84%
So according the
functional scans,

00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:31.210 align:middle line:84%
as the brain begins to
quiet-- the frontal lobe

00:29:31.210 --> 00:29:33.940 align:middle line:84%
begins to quiet down the
rest of the brain, that's

00:29:33.940 --> 00:29:36.550 align:middle line:84%
when you begin to no
longer feel your body.

00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:38.520 align:middle line:90%
You lose track of your identity.

00:29:38.520 --> 00:29:40.315 align:middle line:84%
You forget about your
external environment.

00:29:40.315 --> 00:29:41.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what
the zone is, isn't it?

00:29:41.680 --> 00:29:43.090 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: That
zone, then flow,

00:29:43.090 --> 00:29:46.570 align:middle line:84%
that moment where the thought
is you're one with something,

00:29:46.570 --> 00:29:48.380 align:middle line:84%
there's a biological
reason for it.

00:29:48.380 --> 00:29:50.380 align:middle line:84%
And that's when the frontal
lobe, the forebrain,

00:29:50.380 --> 00:29:52.010 align:middle line:90%
begins to get in control.

00:29:52.010 --> 00:29:54.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how do you
suggest that people--

00:29:54.130 --> 00:29:56.710 align:middle line:84%
someone's asking--
Kate on Facebook--

00:29:56.710 --> 00:29:58.670 align:middle line:84%
shake things up to
break these habits?

00:29:58.670 --> 00:30:01.420 align:middle line:84%
How do you interrupt
the pattern?

00:30:01.420 --> 00:30:03.820 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well, this
is the exciting part--

00:30:03.820 --> 00:30:05.890 align:middle line:84%
this is an exciting
time to be alive.

00:30:05.890 --> 00:30:08.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you're happy with
your life the way it is,

00:30:08.590 --> 00:30:10.130 align:middle line:90%
that's wonderful.

00:30:10.130 --> 00:30:13.030 align:middle line:84%
But know I think that people
secretly believe that they

00:30:13.030 --> 00:30:14.330 align:middle line:90%
could always do a better job.

00:30:14.330 --> 00:30:16.292 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if I'm
talking to prison inmates

00:30:16.292 --> 00:30:17.250 align:middle line:90%
or I'm talking to CEOs.

00:30:17.250 --> 00:30:19.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you think
the brain really

00:30:19.090 --> 00:30:21.950 align:middle line:84%
has a desire to achieve a
higher order of some kind?

00:30:21.950 --> 00:30:22.750 align:middle line:90%
Do you really?

00:30:22.750 --> 00:30:23.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: I don't
think it's the brain.

00:30:23.710 --> 00:30:26.260 align:middle line:84%
I think it's you and I that
use the brain to create

00:30:26.260 --> 00:30:27.430 align:middle line:90%
different levels of mind.

00:30:27.430 --> 00:30:29.230 align:middle line:90%
And so the brain is highly--

00:30:29.230 --> 00:30:30.940 align:middle line:90%
it's full of water.

00:30:30.940 --> 00:30:32.290 align:middle line:90%
It's 78% water.

00:30:32.290 --> 00:30:33.820 align:middle line:90%
It's very plastic.

00:30:33.820 --> 00:30:36.730 align:middle line:84%
And to shake things
up, of course,

00:30:36.730 --> 00:30:38.890 align:middle line:84%
is to begin to do
the unpredictable,

00:30:38.890 --> 00:30:42.340 align:middle line:84%
to begin to step outside of
the familiar, learn new things,

00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:46.030 align:middle line:84%
apply them, begin to
have new experiences,

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:48.700 align:middle line:84%
and see if those
experiences lead to wisdom,

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:50.590 align:middle line:84%
give you a greater
understanding.

00:30:50.590 --> 00:30:53.020 align:middle line:84%
And become a scientist
in your life.

00:30:53.020 --> 00:30:56.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I love to begin to
make changes inside of me

00:30:56.830 --> 00:30:58.790 align:middle line:84%
and then look for the
results outside of me.

00:30:58.790 --> 00:31:00.370 align:middle line:90%
I love to see--

00:31:00.370 --> 00:31:02.900 align:middle line:84%
if I'm changing my
mind in some way,

00:31:02.900 --> 00:31:05.770 align:middle line:84%
then let's see if there's
evidence in my life.

00:31:05.770 --> 00:31:08.170 align:middle line:84%
Think about it-- how do
you know that you're you?

00:31:08.170 --> 00:31:12.640 align:middle line:84%
You look in the mirror and you
see your face, that reflection.

00:31:12.640 --> 00:31:15.125 align:middle line:90%
So how does the ego know itself?

00:31:15.125 --> 00:31:16.000 align:middle line:90%
It's the environment.

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:18.520 align:middle line:84%
So your environment then
reflects back to you

00:31:18.520 --> 00:31:19.450 align:middle line:90%
your level of mind.

00:31:19.450 --> 00:31:23.350 align:middle line:84%
So if you can change your
mind then, do it, and see,

00:31:23.350 --> 00:31:26.050 align:middle line:84%
well, let's see, if I change
up something inside of me,

00:31:26.050 --> 00:31:27.642 align:middle line:84%
if there's some
effect outside of me.

00:31:27.642 --> 00:31:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And begin to play with
that a little bit,

00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:29.740 align:middle line:90%
and see where it takes you.

00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:31.073 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Experiment a little bit.

00:31:31.073 --> 00:31:34.630 align:middle line:84%
There's a clip that Dr.
Joe did from the movie,

00:31:34.630 --> 00:31:36.940 align:middle line:84%
"People Versus the
Power of Illusion."

00:31:36.940 --> 00:31:38.440 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: "The
State of Illusion."

00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:39.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: "The State
of Illusion,"--

00:31:39.130 --> 00:31:40.810 align:middle line:84%
"People Versus the
State of Illusion,"

00:31:40.810 --> 00:31:44.080 align:middle line:84%
and it talks all
about how we are

00:31:44.080 --> 00:31:46.790 align:middle line:84%
able to change and the
addictions to the old habits

00:31:46.790 --> 00:31:47.590 align:middle line:90%
that we have.

00:31:47.590 --> 00:31:49.750 align:middle line:90%
Let's see that clip.

00:31:49.750 --> 00:31:53.605 align:middle line:10%
>> The person who memorizes
a great golf swing,

00:31:53.605 --> 00:31:55.230 align:middle line:10%
and they put all
their attention on it,

00:31:55.230 --> 00:31:56.938 align:middle line:10%
and they practice it
