and why it's difficult.

00:33:14.150 --> 00:33:16.530 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned at the
very beginning the show.

00:33:16.530 --> 00:33:19.790 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to reaffirm
by saying change is difficult.

00:33:19.790 --> 00:33:22.790 align:middle line:84%
And I get kind of stuck by that,
because I would like to tell

00:33:22.790 --> 00:33:26.750 align:middle line:90%
myself, as if change is easy.

00:33:26.750 --> 00:33:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
once again, that's

00:33:28.590 --> 00:33:30.590 align:middle line:84%
one of the reasons I wrote
"Breaking the Habit,"

00:33:30.590 --> 00:33:34.460 align:middle line:84%
is because once you
understand the how to,

00:33:34.460 --> 00:33:37.430 align:middle line:84%
that you can't use your
conscious mind to do this,

00:33:37.430 --> 00:33:39.660 align:middle line:84%
you have to move beyond
the analytical mind.

00:33:39.660 --> 00:33:41.780 align:middle line:84%
And when you understand
brainwave patterns,

00:33:41.780 --> 00:33:44.930 align:middle line:84%
and when you slip into a
different state of mind,

00:33:44.930 --> 00:33:46.880 align:middle line:90%
that it's easier to do it.

00:33:46.880 --> 00:33:49.085 align:middle line:90%
Because most people then--

00:33:49.085 --> 00:33:52.490 align:middle line:84%
95% of who we are by the
time we're 35 years old

00:33:52.490 --> 00:33:55.010 align:middle line:84%
is a set of memorized
habits and behaviors

00:33:55.010 --> 00:33:57.270 align:middle line:84%
that become part of our
identity or personality.

00:33:57.270 --> 00:34:00.590 align:middle line:84%
So 5% of the conscious
mind is trying

00:34:00.590 --> 00:34:04.220 align:middle line:84%
to change 95% of what
we've memorized, hardwired,

00:34:04.220 --> 00:34:06.080 align:middle line:90%
become addicted to emotionally.

00:34:06.080 --> 00:34:09.110 align:middle line:84%
So the person may want
to think positively,

00:34:09.110 --> 00:34:11.389 align:middle line:84%
but they've been feeling
negatively and oiling

00:34:11.389 --> 00:34:13.909 align:middle line:84%
those programs for
the last 25 years.

00:34:13.909 --> 00:34:17.360 align:middle line:84%
They might want a new
life with new conditions.

00:34:17.360 --> 00:34:19.460 align:middle line:10%
And as they use
their conscious mind

00:34:19.460 --> 00:34:21.909 align:middle line:10%
to focus on that, their
subconscious mind,

00:34:21.909 --> 00:34:24.080 align:middle line:10%
they've been programmed
to feel guilty.

00:34:24.080 --> 00:34:25.790 align:middle line:84%
That's mind and
body in opposition.

00:34:25.790 --> 00:34:28.697 align:middle line:84%
We have to begin to recondition
the body to a new mind.

00:34:28.697 --> 00:34:31.280 align:middle line:84%
So change isn't hard, it's just
that you got to get the manual

00:34:31.280 --> 00:34:35.270 align:middle line:84%
to understand how to begin
to unlearn and relearn,

00:34:35.270 --> 00:34:38.485 align:middle line:84%
to break the habit of the old
self and reinvent the new self.

00:34:38.485 --> 00:34:40.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Joe on Facebook is
familiar with the phrase

00:34:40.610 --> 00:34:42.050 align:middle line:90%
